    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL -
        COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS (1X709 MODELS)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS (1X709 MODELS)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft to the rear and insert the countershaft support tool to center the
                shaft in the rear case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m0">Figure 220</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m0" filename="../figg13/G13020m0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 220. Move Countershaft To Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver to start the front bearing in the case bore.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a screwdriver inserted in the countershaft bolt bore to help center the countershaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft forward into the bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end bearing driver and maul to completely seat the front bearing in the case
                bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m1">Figure 221</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m1" filename="../figg13/G13020m1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 221. Seat The Front Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the retainer plate with roll pin in the shaft end hole on the countershaft front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m2">Figure 222</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m2" filename="../figg13/G13020m2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 222. Position The Retainer Plate</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure with a bolt and tighten to 90 to 120 ft-lbs. (122 to 163 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m2">Figure 222</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft support tool from the rear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the larger I.D. lead chamfer to the shaft front, use a flanged-end bearing driver and
                install the rear bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m3">Figure 223</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m3" filename="../figg13/G13020m3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 223. Install Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear snap ring in the countershaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020m4">Figure 224</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020m4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020m4" filename="../figg13/G13020m4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 224. Install Rear Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
